Kasman. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://kasmana.people.cofc.edu/MATHFICT/\">\"Mathematical Fiction\"</a>. Alex Kasman<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">26 April</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Mathematical+Fiction&amp;rft.pub=Alex+Kasman&amp;rft.au=Alex+Kasman&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fkasmana.people.cofc.edu%2FMATHFICT%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematical+fiction\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ams.org/gnews#!news_id=1171\">\"Mathematical Fiction Website Achieves Milestone\"</a>. American Mathematical Society<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 May</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Mathematical+Fiction+Website+Achieves+Milestone&amp;rft.pub=American+Mathematical+Society&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ams.org%2Fgnews%23%21news_id%3D1171&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematical+fiction\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Maya Sharma. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://blogs.ams.org/mathgradblog/2012/09/30/stories-mathematicians-mathematical-fiction-homepage/#sthash.cLdHW0QU.dpbs\">\"Stories for Mathematicians: The Mathematical Fiction Homepage\"</a>. <i>AMS Blogs</i>. American Mathematical Society<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">1 May</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=AMS+Blogs&amp;rft.atitle=Stories+for+Mathematicians%3A+The+Mathematical+Fiction+Homepage&amp;rft.au=Maya+Sharma&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fblogs.ams.org%2Fmathgradblog%2F2012%2F09%2F30%2Fstories-mathematicians-mathematical-fiction-homepage%2F%23sthash.cLdHW0QU.dpbs&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematical+fiction\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mathematical_fiction&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Further reading\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>For a study of the mathematical fiction for senior students and undergraduates see: <cite class=\"citation journal\">Janice Padula. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://files.eric.ed.gov/fulltext/EJ744036.pdf\">\"Mathematical fiction for  senior students and undergraduates: Novels, plays, and film\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>Australian Senior Mathematics Journal</i>. <b>20</b> (2): 36\u201344<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">26 April</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Australian+Senior+Mathematics+Journal&amp;rft.atitle=Mathematical+fiction+for++senior+students+and+undergraduates%3A+Novels%2C+plays%2C+and+film&amp;rft.volume=20&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=36-44&amp;rft.au=Janice+Padula&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ffiles.eric.ed.gov%2Ffulltext%2FEJ744036.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematical+fiction\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li>For a selection of mathematical fiction chosen  with the teaching of mathematics in secondary school in mind: <cite class=\"citation journal\">Janice Padula (2005). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://files.eric.ed.gov/fulltext/EJ743574.pdf\">\"Mathematical Fiction: Its Place in Secondary-School Mathematics Learning\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>Australian Mathematics Teacher</i>. <b>61</b> (4): 6\u201313<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">26 April</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Australian+Mathematics+Teacher&amp;rft.atitle=Mathematical+Fiction%3A+Its+Place+in+Secondary-School+Mathematics+Learning&amp;rft.volume=61&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=6-13&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.au=Janice+Padula&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ffiles.eric.ed.gov%2Ffulltext%2FEJ743574.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematical+fiction\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li>For a discussion of the portrayal of mathematicians in fictional works: <cite class=\"citation journal\">Daniel Dotson (2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://docs.lib.purdue.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1324&amp;context=clcweb\">\"Portrayal of Mathematicians in Fictional Works\"</a>. <i>CLC Web: Comparative Literature  and Culture</i>. <b>8</b> (4)<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">26 April</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=CLC+Web%3A+Comparative+Literature++and+Culture&amp;rft.atitle=Portrayal+of+Mathematicians+in+Fictional+Works&amp;rft.volume=8&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.au=Daniel+Dotson&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.lib.purdue.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D1324%26context%3Dclcweb&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematical+fiction\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li>For an analysis of mathematical fiction with geometrical themes see: <cite class=\"citation book\">Jennifer Rebecca Shloming (2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://academiccommons.columbia.edu/catalog/ac%3A153198\"><i>Analysis of Mathematical Fiction with Geometric Themes</i></a>. Columbia University<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">26 April</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Analysis+of+Mathematical+Fiction+with+Geometric+Themes&amp;rft.pub=Columbia+University&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.au=Jennifer+Rebecca+Shloming&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Facademiccommons.columbia.edu%2Fcatalog%2Fac%253A153198&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMathematical+fiction\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li>For a review of <i>Flatterland</i>: <cite class=\"citation journal\">Jody Trout (April 2012). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ams.org/notices/200204/rev-trout.pdf\">\"Review of Flatterland: Like Flatland,  Only More So\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>Notices of the AMS</i>. <b>49</b> (4): 462\u2013465<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">30 April</span> 2016</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Notices+of+the+AMS&amp;rft.atitle=Review+of+Flatterland%3A+Like+Flatland%2C++Only+More+So&amp;rft.volume=49&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=462-465&amp;rft.date=2012-04&amp;rft.au=Jody+Trout&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ams.org